165    /**
166    * The base class for axes that display dates. You will find it easier to
167    * understand how this axis works if you bear in mind that it really
168    * displays/measures integer (or long) data, where the integers are
169    * milliseconds since midnight, 1-Jan-1970. When displaying tick labels, the
170    * millisecond values are converted back to dates using a
171    * <code>DateFormat</code> instance.
172    * <P>
173    * You can also create a {@link org.jfree.chart.axis.Timeline} and supply in
174    * the constructor to create an axis that only contains certain domain values.
175    * For example, this allows you to create a date axis that only contains
176    * working days.
177    */
